6:
How LONG I have waited for this very
day! To finally face the Vermillion
Knights!
12:
Behold, you stand before the
ALMIGHTY Denah Selphis, servant of
the one and only KING OF VOID AND
DARKNESS!
15:
Come to me, creatures of the abyss!
Obey the call of our Lord and help
me DESTROY his enemies!
18:
Oh god, one of these types. I knew
we'd come across one eventually...
23:
Wait a moment—King of Darkness?
Is that an alias for the Lord of
Shadow? Are you in allegiance with
him?!
28:
Hello. My name is Stella. We do not
wish to fight, so please tell us what
you want.
33:
HMPH! I have but ONE SINGULAR
DESIRE, that being—
35:
Oy, there she is! She's right over
there!
37:
That no-good salvager! We've got
you cornered this time, Denah! Put
your weapons down and come with
us!
39:
Aaaand of course we get dragged
into something.
44:
Grrr. Gosh darn it, I was on a ROLL
there. Way to interrupt me!
47:
Okay, hold on. Ahem.
Ah yes, an excellent chance to
showcase the devastating power
the KING OF VOID AND DARKNESS has
bestowed upon me!
51:
WOE TO YOU, oh enemies mine!
Behold my ultimate ability:
666—the number of the beast!
56:
That knife... It bears no resemblance
to the weapons forged by the
Fiends, and yet... I sense a powerful
dread within it.
59:
W-wait a minute. She has actual
powers?! I thought she was just
role-playing!
63:
TREMBLE before my unbelievably
awesome power! Muahahaha!
67:
Uh, actually... Do you guys happen
to have any food? I'm starving... 
Oh, and I got lost and dropped my
wallet so I have no money, either.
73:
Okay, I'll have the garlic shrimp,
acqua pazza, and... squid ink pasta!
OH, and a beer please—in the
biggest mug you've got!
77:
Help yourself, why don't you... 
Wait a minute—beer? 
Are you even old enough to drink?
82:
Huh? How rude! 
I'll have you know I am a grown 
woman of legal drinking age!
85:
Oh. It's just... Your behavior
suggested otherwise—er, forget I
said that.
89:
Excuuuse me?! Are you calling me
immature?!
94:
Sorry to interrupt, but you didn't
bring us here just to get a free meal,
did you?
98:
Of course not! I mean, the meal's 
a BIG bonus, but that's not all!
100:
Here's the thing... I want you guys to
introduce me to the mermaids!
104:
I see. Let me see if I've got your story
straight. Ever since you obtained the
so-called "Void Knife", you've been
hearing a strange voice whisper to
you.
106:
Said voice belongs to the "King of
Void and Darkness", to whom you
pledge allegiance and are intent on
meeting.
108:
And to do that, you need to travel to
the "abyss"—far in the depths of the
ocean.
110:
Standing in your way were the
Gaean military and the pirates, from
whom you heard rumors of the
mermaids—and of course, us.
113:
That was one heck of a plot
summary, Light, wow.
117:
No kidding! And it's all accurate, too!
Anyway... The SACRED REALM of my
king lies on the edge of the northern
abyss!
123:
I couldn't find my way out of a paper
bag. Even if you told me where my
Lord is, I wouldn't be able to find
him...
126:
So... Please, help me out here! Won't
you guide me to where the
mermaids are?
130:
I can't in good conscience agree to
this. The power that blade has given
you is immense—and potentially
dangerous.
135:
Pleeeaase! I'm begging you here, 
I'll do ANYTHING—even chores!
140:
I mean, I guess it can't hurt to just
take her to meet the mermaids,
right?
142:
We don't have to help her with this
whole... Void King business or
anything.
147:
You wish to wake the Devourer of
Stars?! Are you out of your MIND?
Have you any idea what that would
mean?!
150:
Devourer of Stars? Just what kind of
power does this "King" of hers hold,
exactly?!
152:
Were he to stir again, the entire
ocean would be in grave peril! 
Nay, it would cease to be!
154:
But that's beside the point. It can't
be done—the Devourer rests beyond
the northern trenches. Even we
mermaids cannot travel there.
155:
You would do best to discard that
knife immediately, young one. For
your own good.
158:
Hmm. All right! Thanks anyway, old
man. I guess I'll just think of another
way!
161:
If even the mermaids can't go
there... I suppose I'll have to talk to
my contacts again and look for new
info...
165:
R-really? You're still not gonna give
up?
169:
Why would I give up? Plan A didn't
work out, sure, but so what?
172:
And the whole "throw the knife
away" lecture? I've heard that a
million times! Heck, that's the whole
reason why the Gaean Navy is after
me!
175:
Anyway, there's no way I'm about to
call it quits. Finding my Lord is my
life's work—my DESTINY!
177:
Never again will I utter the words
"give up"—not until I am in his dark
presence!
MUAHAHAHAHA!
182:
I wonder what Denah ended up
doing after all that? Think she's still
searching for her... Dark Lord or
whatever?
185:
She doesn't strike me as the type to
sulk around and be idle. She's surely
up to something.
196:
Muahaha! It seems that the ABYSSAL
FORCES have ordained our paths to
cross again!
199:
Before you stands Denah Selphis,
chosen Maiden of the one and only
KING OF VOID AND DARKNESS!
202:
Rejoice! I have come to liberate this
city in the name of my Lord!
205:
Cool.
So, uh, how exactly did you find your
way here?
209:
Uh, that would be the
aforementioned "abyssal forces"
—a mermaid from the depths 
named Amelia!
212:
And I quote, "Your King is like, sealed
away at the bottom of the ocean?
Wow, that's crazy, I'll totally help you
out!"
221:
This is Starview Village. We welcome
you, Denah.
225:
Nice! I'll be sticking around until I find
another way of meeting my Lord!
230:
Hold on a second—I haven't agreed
to this!
